Data layer chunk B: interceptors, effective-dating filter, ADR 0005

Interceptors (registered in order; first runs before second):
- StandardFieldsInterceptor stamps CreatedBy/Utc, ModifiedBy/Utc,
  RowVersion on every save touching AuditableEntity
- AuditSaveChangesInterceptor writes one AuditLogEntry per CUD,
  shared timestamp + correlation id across one SaveChanges
  - Hard-delete signaled via EF Core EntityState.Deleted
  - Loop prevention: AuditLogEntry rows are themselves not audited
  - JSON via System.Text.Json; DictionaryKeyPolicy.CamelCase

Services hosts cross-cutting abstractions (Data -> Services, not the
reverse):
- IClock + SystemClock
- ICurrentUserAccessor
- IAuditCorrelationProvider
- ITemporalResolver + CurrentTimeTemporalResolver

Effective-dating filter inlined in DbContext.OnModelCreating:
- References this.AsOfUtc on the DbContext
- EF Core parameterizes DbContext member access at query time
- Live re-evaluation verified by mutable-resolver test

ADRs:
- 0005 (Accepted): closure-capture gotcha for query filters;
  forbidden patterns; the test that catches regressions
- 0003 updated: dependency direction subsection documenting
  Data -> Services inversion

20 new integration tests (4 + 6 + 2 + 4 + 4) -> 126 total
